                                <p>Surah Al-Fatihah is the first chapter of the Quran and is recited in every unit of the Muslim prayer. It establishes the most fundamental principles of Islam - the oneness of Allah, His mercy, and the Day of Judgment. The Surah is a prayer to Allah for guidance on the straight path, which is the path of those whom Allah has blessed, not the path of those who earned His anger or went astray.</p>
